My Dad and my girls.  Myron Wells played accordion in an accordion marching band in high school in Oregon.  Later, he had a rather stressful job as a pastor for nearly 60 years.  I remember the sound of the accordion coming off of the back porch as he would play in solitude.  I think it calmed him.  In his adult years, he didn’t really play or perform for others.  It was something he did for himself.  And it brought him some peace and joy.  Lately, he’s been breaking it out more.  He and mom will play through some old church hymns.. my mom on piano and my dad on accordion.  My sisters @donellelo and @tamila_zahrndt also jammed with him recently.  Pretty cool.  The accordion will always be a very nostalgic sound to me.  Dad recently has been gifting us kids his accordions.  He has collected several over the years. It seems like a rather challenging instrument to play… but I need to get after it.  Thanks Dad for playing music for the sake of music.  Sometimes, as a professional musician, the lines get blurry and I can forget to just enjoy it for the peace, joy and love it brings.

Days I Will Remember!  Kind of fun to use my own song for this reel.  It is how I feel 😍. COSTA RICA is unbelievable! Thanks Todd Gabello and Agiliti for the amazing gig. (And thanks Tamila and Nana for taking care of our kiddos so we could go!) We went to Guanacaste, Tabacon, and the Peace Lodge.  PURA VIDA!  Most of the animals in this video were in the wild, but for those in captivity I wanted to share the following info.  La Paz Waterfall Gardens says, “None of the animals that you will see in this Wildlife Refuge have been taken from their natural habitat. They were entrusted to our care by the Costa Rican Wildlife Ministry (MINAET), most of them were illegally held as pets when the Wildlife Ministry found and confiscated them. For various reasons these animals cannot be released back in to the wild.” PURA VIDA! If you can ever get to Costa Rica, DO IT!!

There are people in the world that light up every room they walk into. Maybe it’s because of their infectious joy.  Their sense of humor.  Their grace.  Their compassion.  Their ability to champion any and everyone they encounter.  Their faith.  Their beauty. Their zest for life and fun.  Or maybe all of these things.  Like with our amazing friend @tishafalconlehfeldt She is one of my wife’s dearest friends.  She’s been diagnosed with a very rare cancer and we are desperately praying and thinking of her all the time.  All my praying friends, please join me in prayers for Tisha, her husband Jason and their family.  The world is a radically better place because Tisha is here. ❤️❤️ @teamtisha21

You’re about to see a lot of these from artists.  I think the main reason is.. sometimes as a creator of music, it’s easy to get overwhelmed and doubt yourself.  Am I making a difference? Does my music impact people?  Should I keep at it? These are questions that I and so many of us ask ourselves.  This information really helps me keep plugging away.  And it’s encouraging.  Thanks @spotify for offering this info to the artists.  Thank you for listening wherever you listen. It means so much to me.

The Wells girls and I hope you have a wonderful 2024.  If you look around yourself and see a lack of beauty in the world this year, do something beautiful.  Like calling an old friend.  Or paying for someone’s meal. Or helping someone that needs help.  Or speaking your truth.  Or forgiving someone that hurt you.  Beauty is available everywhere we turn.  With Love, Tyrone
